{% if file_type == "handler" or file_type == "route" %}
## Focus: HTTP Handler
- Input validation on all request parameters
- Output encoding to prevent XSS
- Authentication/authorization checks
- CSRF protection if stateful
- Rate limiting considerations
{% elif file_type == "model" or file_type == "database" %}
## Focus: Data Layer
- SQL injection (parameterized queries, not string concatenation)
- Mass assignment (only expected fields accepted)
- Sensitive data exposure (passwords hashed, tokens not logged)
{% elif file_type == "config" %}
## Focus: Configuration
- Secrets not hardcoded (use environment variables)
- Debug mode not enabled by default
- Secure defaults (HTTPS, strict CORS)
{% else %}
## General Review
- Injection risks (SQL, command, template)
- Exposed secrets or credentials
- Missing input validation at system boundaries
- Insecure cryptography
- Path traversal
- Error messages that leak internal details
{% endif %}

## What NOT to flag
- Internal utility functions with no user-facing input do not have injection risks.
- Code that calls a well-tested library function does not need to re-validate what the library validates.
- Theoretical risks that require an attacker to already have code execution are not useful findings.

